05812nam a22009375i 9783110919813DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20112006gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831109198137 a10.1515/97831109198132doi  a(DE-B1597)56830  a(OCoLC)979629042  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP140b.W36 2006eb 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a417/.7222  aET 1702rvk0(DE-625)rvk/27949:1 aWanner, Dieter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Power of Analogy :bAn Essay on Historical Linguistics /cDieter Wanner.  aReprint 2011 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2011] 4c©2006  a1 online resource (330 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Linguistics. Studies and Monographs [TiLSM] ,x1861-4302 ;v1700 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn The Power of Anology, Dieter Wanner argues for reinstating historical linguistics, especially in (morpho-)syntax, as constitutive of any theoretical account of language. In the first part, he provides a critique of some foundational concepts of an object-oriented linguistic perspective, questioning the distinction between synchrony and diachrony, dichotomous parametrization, grammaticality judgments, and formal generalization. Instead, the immanent perspective of the linguistic individual, licensed by broad cognitive functions, highlights such relegated dimensions as similarity, (surface) redundancy, frequency of form, and social and environmental conditions on language use. In the second part, Dieter Wanner relies on a systematic construct of analogy as the dynamic force enabling language, tying together acquisition, language use, and linguistic change. Such analogy is pervasive, driven by local models, and inevitably spreading through the social web of linguistic practice. The unpredictability, incompletion, and typical slowness of change thereby become the norm, while categorical closure remains a marked possibility. The framework of "Soft Syntax" spells out an operative model for syntax relying on precedence, cohesion, dependence, agreement, constructional identity, and concatenation. These six dimensions and their interplay undergo a detailed exploration of their diachronic operation and implications, applying them to typical examples taken from the history of the Romance languages. The openness of the framework enables diachronic linguistics to approach old problems in a new light and to ask new questions about the mechanics and nature of language change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAnalogy (Linguistics). 0aHistorical linguistics. 4aRomance languages. 4aRomanische Völker /Sprache. 4aSprachgeschichte. 4ahistorical linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aHistorical linguistics.  aRomance languages.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2006z9783110277128oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2006z978311027718008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2006z978311027715908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2006z9783110276893